        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Continuous Monitoring of Third-Party AI Risk"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A point-in-time TPRM assessment goes stale the moment it is completed. Third-party AI risk is dynamic: Anthropic publishes model updates, API terms change, security vulnerabilities are discovered, and vendor financial stability can shift. Continuous monitoring converts the TPRM programme from an annual checkbox into a live risk sensor that detects changes between formal re-assessments."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For Claude specifically, three categories of change are especially consequential: model version updates (which can alter output characteristics), usage policy changes (which can restrict or expand permitted use cases), and API availability degradation (which affects business continuity commitments)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Continuous Third-Party AI Risk Monitoring Signals",
          "title": null
        }
      },
